---
const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'What is Illoominate?',
    answer: 'Illoominate is a feedback management platform that helps product teams collect, organize, and prioritize user feedback. It includes feature voting, public roadmaps, AI-powered insights, and automatic notifications when features ship.',
  },
  {
    question: 'When will Illoominate launch?',
    answer: 'We\'re currently in development and plan to launch our beta in early 2025. Join the waitlist to get early access and help shape the product with your feedback.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Is there a free tier?',
    answer: 'Yes! We\'ll offer a generous free tier that includes core features for small teams and open source projects. Paid plans will add advanced features like AI insights, custom domains, and priority support.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How does the referral system work?',
    answer: 'When you join the waitlist, you get a unique referral link. For each person who signs up and verifies using your link, you move up in the queue. Top referrers get VIP early access!',
  },
  {
    question: 'What integrations will you support?',
    answer: 'We\'re building integrations with Linear, Jira, GitHub, Notion, Slack, Intercom, and more. Have a specific integration in mind? Let us know when you join!',
  },
  {
    question: 'Can I import existing feedback?',
    answer: 'Absolutely. We\'ll support importing from spreadsheets, GitHub Issues, Canny, and other feedback tools. Migration should be seamless.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How does AI help with feedback?',
    answer: 'Our AI automatically detects duplicate requests, categorizes feedback by theme, analyzes sentiment, and surfaces trending topics. It saves hours of manual organization.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Is my data secure?',
    answer: 'Security is a top priority. We use industry-standard encryption, comply with GDPR and SOC 2, and never share your data with third parties. Enterprise plans will include SSO and additional security features.',
  },
];
---

<section id="faq" class="section-padding bg-slate-900">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <span class="inline-block px-4 py-1 bg-slate-700 text-slate-300 rounded-full text-sm font-medium mb-4">FAQ</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">
        Got questions? We've got answers. Can't find what you're looking for? Reach out!
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      {faqs.map((faq, index) => (
        <details class="group bg-slate-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm border border-slate-700 overflow-hidden">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 hover:bg-slate-700 transition-colors">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white pr-4">{faq.question}</h3>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-slate-400 flex-shrink-0 transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-slate-400">
            {faq.answer}
          </div>
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
